The graph below best illustrates which of the following? <image 1>

A. The spacing effect
B. The impact of elaborative rehearsal on recall
C. Hermann Ebbinghaus's forgetting curve
D. The effect of visual imagery on retention
E. The serial position effect

The graph illustrates the serial position effect, which describes how the position of an item in a sequence affects the likelihood of its recall. The graph shows higher recall rates for items at the beginning (primacy) and end (recency) of a list, with lower recall for items in the middle (intermediate). This pattern is characteristic of the serial position effect.

So, the correct answer is:

E. The serial position effect
